column5: A skim of ice on the bay close to shore. Open water for most of the bay still, some open spots near marina.  Don't rush it, they're just fish.
brb I'm going to drive out and test the ice.
Me first! ME FIRST!   I've got more ice in my "frost free" frezzer.
K Bay looked mostly skimmed over this morning.  That one usually crazy bugger will be out soon, off the water fountain.
Innisfil beach park it's frozen all the way to the islands But I would not be walking on it right now
You called it last weekend Terry!!
*hops on ATV*
There was no ice in the bay 3 days ago. The skim of ice isn't even out to Johnson's Beach. The rest of the bay is wide open and there are open spots in/near the marina.
K Bay looked mostly skimmed over this morning.  That one usually crazy bugger will be out soon, off the water fountain.  YUP
Few hundred feet of not-safe ice off shore in KBay now. An inch or two at most.
They are out there this morning.
It doesn't suprise me!
I may just wait a day or 2
Me too!  Water wings and a swim suit.
When the huts are out on Minet, I'll be there. No way before.
